## The Five Tools (All Share One Data Model)

DataTools Pro is a suite of five interconnected tools. They operate on the **same underlying data graph**, stored as a relational database. Changes in one tool are reflected across others.

| Tool | What It Does |
|---|---|
| **Metrics Glossary** | Defines, documents, and distributes Salesforce business metrics. Features the patent-pending **Metrics Analyst** that auto-generates a metrics glossary by reverse-engineering existing dashboards. Solves the "multiple versions of truth" problem by detecting metric aliases and conflicts across teams. |
| **Entity Relationship Diagram (ERD)** | Generates a live, interactive, business-oriented ERD from your Salesforce org in one click. Color-coded by relationship type. Drill from objects into fields. Export to PNG/SVG. Designed for visual storytelling — accessible to both technical and business users. |
| **Data Dictionary** | Live connected documentation of Salesforce objects and fields aligned to business initiatives; tracks what changed and the reporting/analytics impact |
| **Data Migration Tools** | Object and field mapping process management; replaces spreadsheets; generates SQL for ETL during migrations |
| **Report Management & Repository** | Governs the lifecycle of Salesforce reports and dashboards; enables categorization, searching, and adoption tracking |

See deep-dive docs in `docs/product/tools/` for each tool.

