## Shared Data Model Concepts

All five tools operate on the same underlying entities. Key shared concepts:

- **Salesforce Org** — the connected Salesforce instance (multi-org support may exist)
- **Salesforce Object** — standard or custom Salesforce object (e.g. `Account`, `Opportunity`)
- **Salesforce Field** — a field on an object
- **Business Topic** — a grouping/categorization concept used to organize objects, metrics, and ERDs
- **Metric** — a defined, documented business metric tied to Salesforce fields/reports
- **Migration Project** — a data migration initiative with source-to-target mappings
- **Report / Dashboard** — a Salesforce report or dashboard under governance

See `docs/architecture/data-model.md` and `.cursor/rules/data-model.mdc` for the full entity map.

