## Key Business Rules

- All data is scoped to an **Organization** (multi-tenant, row-level isolation)
- A Salesforce Org is connected via OAuth as a **Salesforce Connected App**
- Objects and fields are sourced from the live Salesforce org (not manually entered)
- Business Topics are user-defined grouping labels applied across all tools
- The same Salesforce Object/Field can appear in the Dictionary, ERD, Metrics Glossary, AND Migration Tools simultaneously — they share the same record

---

## What This Is NOT

- Not a general-purpose BI tool (no drag-and-drop chart builder)
- Not a Salesforce admin panel (no object/field creation — reads from Salesforce, doesn't write schema)
- Not a standalone ETL tool (Migration Tools generates SQL mapping guidance, doesn't execute migrations)
- Not limited to one Salesforce org per account (multi-org is a consideration)

